verbose_text: Some studies have found little association between SRRs and FSH levels, with FSH levels less than 15 IU/mL having a SRR of 51%, FSH levels between 15-30 IU/mL having a SRR of 60%, FSH levels 31-45 IU/mL having a SRR of 67%, and FSH levels greater than 45 IU/mL having a SRR of 60%, other studies have demonstrated lower SRRs among men with higher FSH levels.
